briefTitle: Immuno,Safety of GSK Vaccine 134612 Given at Age of 12-15 Months 15-18 Months Post-priming With GSK Vaccine 792014
officialTitle: Immunogenicity and Safety Study of a Booster Dose of GSK Biologicals' Meningococcal Vaccine 134612 Given at 12-15 Months of Age or at 15-18 Months of Age (Co-administered With Infanrix®) in Primed Healthy Toddlers.
summary: The purpose of the study is to characterize the immunogenicity \& safety of a booster dose of GSK Biologicals' meningococcal vaccine 134612 given at 12-15 months of age or at 15-18 months of age (co-administered with Infanrix®) in healthy toddlers primed with GSK Biological's Hib-meningococcal vaccine 792014. This study is single-blinded for the primary phase and open-label for the booster phase.

primaryOutcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Serum Bactericidal Activity Using Human Complement (hSBA) Antibody Titers for N. Meningitidis Serogroups A(MenA), W-135(MenW-135), C(MenC) and Y(MenY) Greater Than or Equal to Protocol Specified Cut-off Value in Nimenrix 1 Group
primaryOutcome.timeFrame: One month post vaccination at 12-15 months of age (Month 11)
